  <h1> Avocado Tuna Salad Recipe </h1>
  <p> <em> This avocado tuna salad uses creamy avocado instead  of mayo for a fresh and 
    easy twist of the classic. 
    Red Onion and celery add some crunch, while lemon juice give it some zing.
      Is quic to make and very healthy ğŸ˜‹</em> </p> 
  <h2> Ingredients</h2>
  <ul>
    <!-- Listing the ingredients for the tuna salad -->
    <li> 1 tuna can</li>
    <li> 1/2 ripe avocado, roughly chopped</li>
    <li> 2 eggs </li>
    <li> 2 tablespoons yogurt </li>
    <li> 1/2 cup minced celery </li>
    <li> 1/4 cup minced red onion </li>
    <li> 1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil </li>
    <li> 2 teapsoons lemon juice </li>
    <li> 1 teaspoon lemon zest </li>
    <li> 2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro or parsley</li>
    <li> 1/2 teaspoonkosher salt </li>
    <li> freshly ground black pepper </li>
  </ul>
    <img src="ingredients2.jpg" alt = "Ingredients">
